      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TATOOINE (1) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (22.81) at Gosford behind Zipping Klimenko in a Grade 5. Took the lead and boxed on but run over. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Can measure up this time. HECTIC BLUE (2) was a winner (23.24) at Maitland two back but out of the placings last time when 7th there. Can measure up this time. SUPER QUALITY (7) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fourth (23.13) last time in a Grade 5 at Gosford. Form here at the trip sound including five wins. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Cannot be taken lightly. DASHING MIMCO (8) form at this distance reads well.",
